Good afternoon from Huntington Schools! Just a few reminders:
Tomorrow, all grades will be in attendance. All students are required to wear a mask k-12 while riding the bus and inside the building. School hours are as follows:
HS/MS is in session from 7:45 AM to 1:55 PM
Drop off time begins at 7:40 AM (doors will not unlock until 7:40)
Pick up time begins at 1:55 PM

Elementary is in session from 9:00 AM to 2:55 PM
Drop off time begins at 8:45 AM
Pick up time begins at 2:45 PM

When dropping off your child, please have them ready to exit the car so we can keep traffic moving at an acceptable speed. We do appreciate your cooperation and patience as we work though some of these changes. We have had a great two days and look forward to an outstanding year with your children.

Go Green!

Huntington Local Elementary School
August 24 at 3:51 PM ·

Huntington Elementary is offering Google Classroom training for parents. This training is for any parent that wishes to learn about Google Classroom. Every teacher this year will be using Google Classroom to post their daily activities and assignments. Elementary Students that are attending in person will be following the traditional methods while at school but will be taught how to access Google Classroom. If the school is closed for an extended period of time during the 2020-2021 school year, all students will transition to Google Classroom while at home. Please click the link below to register for a training time. You may also call the elementary office at 740-663-2191 to register for a session. Each session will be limited to the number of participants permitted. Please limit your registration to one parent per family. Thank you!

Register Here: https://forms.gle/tsreDAK5Fq9qdP3m8

post_text: Good evening, I hope everyone is enjoying their summer and staying safe during this time. I wanted to take a minute and update our community on a few items concerning the restart of school this fall. First, we will be returning to school with a few calendar changes. Teachers will come back Tuesday August 18 and students will begin coming back Monday August 24th on a staggered start. Kindergarten and all even grade levels will begin in session on the 24th and all odd grade levels will begin on the 25th and then all grades will be in regular session on Wednesday August 26th according to original school calendar. Our administration and staff are in the process of finalizing a safe start… More

Huntington Local School District Staff and Administration are looking forward to welcoming students back to school in the Fall. Our students, staff, and families have done an amazing job with remote teaching and learning. We are working on plans for re-opening school buildings in the 2020-21 school year and are exploring options based on guidance from our local and state officials. To best plan, we would like to gather your input. Please complete this survey to help us understand what is most important to your family for when we return to school in the fall. Thank you for your participation.

Click below to complete the survey:

Attention all High School Students:
Locker clean out for High School students will follow the schedule listed. You should have a mask or other face covering when you enter the building. Please follow all precautions of social distancing while in the building. Only ten students will be permitted in the building at one time. Again, please follow the schedule below so we can limit the number of people on campus at a given point in time.

Freshmen and Sophomores:
Monday, May 4th: 9:00 am-1:00 pm, 6:30 pm-8:00 pm

Juniors and Seniors:
Tuesday, May 5th: 9:00 am -1:00 pm, 6:00 pm-7:30 pm

Any student that couldn’t attend Monday or Tuesday:
Wednesday. May 6th: 9:00 am -1:00 pm

Students can also turn in finished work which will be counted toward their pass/fail grade for the fourth nine week grading period.
There will be tables set up in Room 118 for return of completed assignments or school owned property (books, calculators, etc...) if not needed to complete any other assignments.

GO GREEN!

post_text: Good afternoon! This message is to inform you that Huntington Local Schools will be conducting its regular scheduled board meeting tonight at 5:30 pm. If you wish to actively participate to this meeting, you may call 1-347-790-1221 and enter the pin number 915460996 and then the # key. This gives you the ability to listen live to our meeting without being in attendance. The meeting room will be closed due to the COVID 19 restrictions and the practice of social distancing. If you would like to address the board publicly, please follow our procedures by calling the district office to fill out the necessary form. Once the form has been submitted, we will place you on the agenda under our recognition portion of the meeting. If you need further assistance or have questions regarding tonight’s meeting, please feel free to call the district office or email pete.ruby@huntsmen.org. Have a great Week. Go Green!

Message from Pete Ruby, Superintedent of Huntington Local Schools:
This message is in regards to the current Coronavirus situation happening across our state and the nation. As most of you are already aware, the Governor has shut down all K-12 facilities in the entire state. As a result of that shut down, Huntington Local Schools will not be in session beginning Monday March 16, 2020. This shut down will remain in effect until Friday April 3, 2020 with students returning to class on Monday April 6, 2020. Our teaching staff will report on Monday to finalize all grades for the end of the 3rd nine weeks and begin preparing educational materials that will help keep your child engaged in… More

post_text: Due to large number of students being affected by illness, Huntington Local Schools will be closed Wednesday, January 29th, Thursday, January 30th and Friday, January 31st. All practices and home ball games will be canceled. Buildings will be closed to staff and community so that our custodial staff may thoroughly disinfect all areas of the district. If your student is running a fever or displays flu-like symptoms, offer plenty of liquids. Fever which is common with the flu, can lead to dehydration. Offer plain water, ice pops, and icy drinks to your child. If symptoms persist, please seek medical attention. More information on influenza can be found on the CDC website: https://www.cdc.gov/flu/highrisk/children.htm
